		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Sacred Band of Thebes</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>Sacred Band of <a href="/wiki/Ancient_Thebes_(Boeotia)" title="Ancient Thebes (Boeotia)">Thebes</a></b> (<a href="/wiki/Ancient_Greek" title="Ancient Greek">ancient Greek</a>: <span lang="grc" xml:lang="grc"><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E1%BC%B1%CE%B5%CF%81%CF%8C%CF%82" class="extiw" title="wikt:ἱερός">'Ιερός</a> <a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%CE%BB%CF%8C%CF%87%CE%BF%CF%82" class="extiw" title="wikt:λόχος">Λόχος</a> τῶν <a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%CE%98%E1%BF%86%CE%B2%CE%B1%CE%B9" class="extiw" title="wikt:Θῆβαι">Θηβῶν</a></span> Hierós <a href="/wiki/Lokhos" title="Lokhos">Lókhos</a> tón Thebón) was a troop of picked soldiers, numbering 150 age-structured pairs, which formed the elite force of the Theban army in the <a href="/wiki/4th_century_BC" title="4th century BC">4th century BC</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> It was organised by the Theban commander <a href="/wiki/Gorgidas" title="Gorgidas">Gorgidas</a> in 378 BC and played a crucial role in the <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Leuctra" title="Battle of Leuctra">Battle of Leuctra</a>. It was completely annihilated, however, by <a href="/wiki/Alexander_the_Great" title="Alexander the Great">Alexander the Great</a> under <a href="/wiki/Philip_II_of_Macedon" title="Philip II of Macedon">Philip II of Macedon</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Chaeronea_(338_BC)" title="Battle of Chaeronea (338 BC)">Battle of Chaeronea</a> in 338 BC.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
